RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GUEST IN MY HEART raced three wide, settled into the middle of a strung out field, advanced at the half mile pole, was in contention at the three eighths pole, challenged for the lead at the quarter pole, easily took command and drew off in the stretch. PEACEFUL MOMENT raced three wide, came from off of the pace, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, had the led at the quarter pole, then flattened out in the stretch. T J'S FIRST raced two wide, was off of the pace early, made one run and closed well, go, up for third. ZEEROCK was off a bit slow, settled well off of the pace, gathered himself up and made one run, closed down the lane. BE BO showed natural speed early and inherited the led along the rail, set the pace while rating in hands, showed the way until after the half mile pole, then stopped. PAYNT THE MOON raced along the rail off of the pace in the middle of the field, then faded after the quarter pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Be Bo
ENTRY.COMMENT: spd, rail, set the pace, then stopped

ENTRY.NAME: Guest in My Heart
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w, mid pack, moved 1/2, challenged 1/4, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: T J's First
ENTRY.OWNER: Roe Steve D and Roe Patricia L

ENTRY.NAME: Zeerock
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, well off the pace, one run

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 65. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since May 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at 1 Mile and 70 Yards) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KINGS WAGER was on the bit and pulling on his reins going into the first turn, drifted into the four path, was brought back in and asked to rate, settled in hands two wide right off of the pace setter, was allowed to draw next to the front runner after the half mile, rated while setting the pace in a set, was asked and responded well at the quarter pole, pulled away, with full of run and took the win gamely. WESTERN STAR raced on the rail in the middle of the field, inched up and improved position on the back side, saved ground on the rail through the turn, closed well under urging in the stretch drive, edged out late to pass a tiring rival and went on to take second place honors. MY PAL SWEET raced two wide, vied for t he lead, took command and set the pace, was joined by an outside foe then set the pace as a set, started to battle through the turn, was under heavy encouragement at the quarter pole but could sustain the bid and gave way in the stretch. MAGIC LIGHTNING raced four wide early on, rated behind the first wall of horses, was kept in place through the turn, was cued at he quarter pole and strongly encouraged, responded well. INFINITESIMAL raced off of the pace early on, maintained position, closed late with a mild bid. JUDGMENTAL raced on the rail, saved ground through out, maintained position but made no impact. FLOWER CAT was sharp out of the gates, pulled his way to the front, was asked to rate and sit off of the pace, finally settled into mid pack in the four path, faded after that. CROSSING IRIS trailed, passed tired rival. RICKY RIGHT showed little.

ENTRY.NAME: Western Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail, stalked, inched up 1/2, out stretch, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Kings Wager
ENTRY.COMMENT: strong, 4w1st, stalked, bid 1/4, ran away with it

ENTRY.NAME: Magic Lightning
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w, 1st turn, rated, btwn, stong urging stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Crossing Iris
ENTRY.OWNER: Salome Robert Joseph and Salome Dana

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 117 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIV'S WILD ACES found herself well off of the pace and racing mid pack early on, raced along the rail, saved ground, found her best stride through the turn where she smartly saved ground and made up lengths on the rail, excelled down the lane, had to stop, angle out into the three path after the sixteenth pole, picked up the pace and drew off like a professional. GIRL LIKES BLING vied for the lead, raced on the rail and set the pace, was joined by another challenger to the outside and was pressured through out, was still on the lead, battled down the lane gamely, had her head in front, was collared by an outside closer and had to settle for second, still ran a very competitive race. PLUM WINE raced four wide, was un hurried for the first half of the race, shuffled back to the rear of the field, launched her bid at the three eighth pole, circled through the turn, was six wide in the upper stretch, found her best stride down the lane, responded well and closed ground quickly when she was asked, nice effort. RONNIE'S DEAL vied for the lead, raced in the two path in between rivals, drew next to the front runner and set the pace with one to her inside and a rival pressuring on the outside, engaged in a battle down the lane with the same horse she was out side of through out, was asked and dug in gamely, fighting for the lead, was collared late by a fast closing foe t the outside and flattened out late. TAKE HER AWAY was off of the pace and four wide early, loomed up to the outside of the early front runners after the half mile pole, maintained position into the stretch but had no late kick. OUR LAST HALF was mid pack and four side, made no impact. COMMUNICATIONISKEY was never involved. DEMOTION stumbled badly out of the gates, recovered and found her legs, tracked the rest of the field greenly.

ENTRY.NAME: Viv's Wild Aces
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail, mid pack, hit stride, closed, stopped, angled out, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Girl Likes Bling
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, led, rail, was pressured, collared late

ENTRY.NAME: Plum Wine
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w, off pace, bid 3/8, shifted 6 wide, closed

ENTRY.NAME: Ronnie's Deal
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, btwn, battled gamely late, collared

ENTRY.NAME: Take Her Away
ENTRY.OWNER: Gillis, Betty J. and Joseph A.
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 4w, maintained position, no late kick

ENTRY.NAME: Our Last Half
ENTRY.OWNER: Tri-Star Racing LLC and Joey Foster Racing & Farm LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VALENTINE ANGEL vied for the lead, raced on the rail, shuffled back and stalked on the back side, launched a bit at the three eighths, edged out into the three path , found clear racing room, came back on her early challenger nearing the eighth pole, over came that rival, and took command of the race and drew off willingly at the sixteenth pole. IRISH WRIT was well off the pace, raced along the rail, angled out into the four path and started to gain ground after the half, improved position through the turn, launched a closing bid after the quarter pole while racing in the six path down the stretch, responded well to encouragement and urging, was able to get up for second. BLUE COWGIRL raced three wide and off of the pace, quickly advanced into a stalking position, continued to gain ground and passed her rivals and took command after the half mile pole, set the fractions until the quarter pole, was run down by the rival she had took the lead from at the half mile pole, relinquished the lead back to that rival and finished flat. BEAUCLAIRE was forwardly placed early, raced two and three wide, was passed by a fst moving outside rival at the half mile pole, tried to g o with that foe but could not sustain the bid and stopped. PREPAID SPECIAL was never involved. DON'T LOOK ETHEL raced in the middle of the field early, raced five wide and faded. WISH FOR CANDY was off of the pace early raced on the rail, showed little.

ENTRY.NAME: Valentine Angel
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, rail, led, shuffled back, edged out 3w, bid1/8, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Writ
ENTRY.OWNER: L and N Racing LLC and Brewster Clark O
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, rail, 4w, improved 1/2, closed determinedly, up of 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Cowgirl
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w, mid pack, moved 1/2, led, caught late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 76. Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since May 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. (If deemed inadvisable b y management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at 1 Mile and 70 Yards) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWEET PERFECTION went wire to wire. HAVE I EVER was racing in the middle of the field in the three path, launched a bid at the quarter pole and closed with determination, gained ground quickly and just missed. TEXAS TIDELANDS stalked the early pace, raced in the three path, loomed next to the front runners after the half mile pole, could not sustain the bid and flattened out in the stretch. C C'S COWGIRL was off of the pace early, was allowed to settle and find her stride while working on the rail, advanced after the half mile marker and improved position into the turn, angled out into the four path in the stretch, found clear racing room, closed well, just had to much to do this time. KENYA STRIKE was mid pack and raced along the rail, smartly saved ground through out, was in contention in the upper stretch, had racing room but no late kick. ABBY THE BULL DAWG trailed early, mild bid. GEE SHE'S PRETTY stalked the front runner, raced on the rail, tired after six furlongs. GIFTED TALENT showed little.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rail trip, in contention, no late kick

ENTRY.NAME: Abby the Bull Dawg
ENTRY.OWNER: Wood David and Dunn John Michael

ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, closed, up in time for second

ENTRY.NAME: Texas Tidelands
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, 3w, moved 1/2, flattened out in the stretch

ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, rail, angled out 4 wide, upper, closed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 6 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JUNE 25, 2022. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OPTIMISTIC stalked the early pace, was asked to rate, grudgingly waited for the cue, was shifted out into the three path at the three eighths pole, willingly passed the front runners, took the lead, showed the way in the stretch but had pressure on the inside and had to battle to stay in front, repelled that foe, then had pressure from the outside, started looking for the wire while that outside foe was closing in, was kept on point and encouraged, kept going and got to the wire in time. FIRST LINE was off of the pace and racing on the rail, was asked to moved at the half, responded well and closed up the fence, shifted out three wide in the turn and was in a full on hand ride, continued to push, and urge, encouraged to keep closing, was kept on point and had the winner in her sights, could not catch the winner today but closed with a great effort. SCREENPLAY vied for the lead, set the first easy fractions, battled into the stretch, faded after the eighth pole, but had done enough early to still hold on to third place honors. POP LIFE was off a bit slow, was well off of the pace, raced on the rail, made one clean run, gained ground, improved position, could not do enough to get with in the tope three but did out finish the rest of the field. MR. UNUSUAL was never involved. MAX PANDOWDY was no menace. CORVETTE SPIRIT made no impact. DONNA'S COURT stalked the front runner from the three path, passed the leader to take command after the half mile marker, then faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Optimistic
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, rail, rated, shifted out 3/8, 3w, battled held on

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Leverett Miller, Linda Miller,Adam Parker & Suzette Parker

ENTRY.NAME: First Line
ENTRY.COMMENT: midpack, rail, 3 wide, turn, strongly encouraged, closed well

ENTRY.NAME: Screenplay
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, rail, pace, saved ground, flattened out a bit

ENTRY.NAME: Pop Life
ENTRY.COMMENT: off the pace, rail, out finished the rest

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $12,500. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 2 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RECKLESS RANSOM raced on the rail, was off of the pace for the first part of the race, found his stride and starting gaining ground after the half, shifted out six wide in the upper stretch, was encouraged and urged, kept on point, closed with every stride, collared the leaders before the sixteenth pole and went on to win easily. WISE ANCHOR was off the pace and three wide early, found his stride and started gaining ground after the half mile marker, shifted out into the six path in the upper stretch and closed with determination, needed more room to get the win but ran a game second. PINCH ME A PENNY was three wide and racing in the middle of the pack, was asked at the half, responded well and challenged for the lead at the three eighths pole, battled into the stretch and down to the eighth pole, was collared by an outside closer and just missed for second. ran very gamely. DOCTOR LEO was off a touch slow, raced on the rail while being last, found his stride, gained ground, was in contention by the quarter pole, closed well in the stretch, looked like he was going to get in the money, but came up short. HALF AGAIN vied for the led, took control of the race and set the fractions, was challenged in the turn and stopped. LILRASCALMAN was never involved. YOUNG TUSCAN flashed early speed. FIERY PLAYBOY stalked the pace setter, raced two wide, drew next tot he leader, matched strides through the turn, then faded. TARGET PRACTICE trailed through out.

ENTRY.NAME: Reckless Ransom
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail, off pace, advanced 1/2, 6 wide, upper, closed, up in time

ENTRY.NAME: Pinch Me a Penny
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w, mid pack, moved 1/2, battted stretch, just missed for 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 8 1 1/16M Turf CR: 90. Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since May 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at 1 1/16 Miles) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOVING LUCKY stalked the early pace while racing in the two path, launched a bid at he three eighths pole, and challenged for the lead, took control before the quarter pole and drew away, started to feel pressure after the sixteenth pole by another rival closing in, was urged and encouraged and held on for the win. LI MU BAI (IRE) stalked from the rail, raced in the second tier, saved ground through out, maintained positioning through the turn, closed ground on the rail, shifted out a bit late and was up for second. ELUSIVE D'ORO stalked from the three path, moved up along side of the pace setter, was challenged by an outside foe, battled with that rival briefly before repelling him, picked up and battled wit an inside closer, gave way to that one and settled for third. DECLARE WAR raced off the pace and launched a mild bid late. CHIEF CHEETAH was mid pack and in the two and three path in between rivals, but had no impact. MONARCH MAN was racing in the four path on the outside, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, and had no kick. DARE TO FAIL was mid pack, stayed on the rail and showed little. TAPIT CITY was never involved. HELIOCHROME set the early pace, raced on the rail and stopped. VETERAN'S HOLIDAY trailed through out.

ENTRY.NAME: Chief Cheetah
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, btwn, had no impact

ENTRY.NAME: Li Mu Bai (IRE)
ENTRY.OWNER: Dunn Christopher T and Peskoff Jeremy
